<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00531</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING THE PACKAGING, USE, SALE, DISTRIBUTION, AND ADVERTISEMENTS OF PRODUCTS WITH HIGH SODIUM CONTENT</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : The Philippine Sodium Labels Act Of 2016</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Mandates food manufacturers to add warning labels to their packaging of processed food products conataining high amount of salt as set by the Bureau of Food and Drugs (BFAD).</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>BATOCABE, RODEL M., GARBIN, ALFREDO JR. A., CO, CHRISTOPHER S.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2016-06-30</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>NATURE : Reform</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Salceda (008 2016-08-09)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2016-07-27</td></tr></table>